che product at the time by the start of world war ii the company was known as atlantic rayon corporation and manufactured parachutes as war production wound down the company started making civilian products as well and was renamed textron “tex for textiles and tron from synthetics such as lustron the company was listed on the nyse in  over the next decade and a half textron purchased various other manufacturing companies in  the company also bought bell aerospace and ezgo the textile division was sold to deering milliken in  later ceos included g william miller – joseph collinson – and robert p straetz – in  textron took on more debt and bought avco a conglomerate almost as big as itself later on james hardymon took over as ceo campbell eraedit hardymon brought in lewis b campbell who became ceo in citation needed starting in  campbell led a companywide restructuring program the share price fell to as low as share in march  after the economic downturn following the collapse of internet companies and the terrorist attacks on the world trade center diminished demand for helicopters and airplanes led to layoffs at cessna and bell helicoptercitation needed in  forbes magazine named campbell as the fifth worstperforming ceo in the country in  the wall street journal reported that campbell had received  in compensation in the form of his use of a corporate jet to travel between his home and office which made him the most expensive ceo in the country in terms of use of jet travel some shareholders have questioned whether it is a good use of shareholder dollars to pay for the personal lifestyle choice of the ceo to live in one state and work in another shares in textron plummeted to as low as  per share in the aftermath of the  economic downturn driving its market capitalization down to just  billioncitation needed while the company lost  of its value in the first ten years of campbells leadership he managed to take home over  million in compensation his salary in  was  million making him the highest paid executive of a conglomerate campbell managed to sell over  million in textron stock in april and may  at prices over  per share after campbelledit scott c donnelly became ceo in december  textron acquired mechtronix in montreal quebec and opinicus in tampa florida in  donnelly combined these flight simulation companies along with textron’s aai logistics  technical services to form tru simulation  training in  on december   textron agreed to purchase beechcraft including the discontinued hawker jet line for  billion the sale was expected to be concluded in the first half of  the company formed a new company called textron aviation to market the products of beechcraft cessna and hawker as individual brands divisions and subsidiariesedit able aerospace servicesedit able aerospace services is an international business and  million aerospace enterprise that is performing more than  proprietary faaapproved repairs on aircraft and components arctic catedit on march   textron bought out arctic cat for usm arctic cat is a manufacturer of snowmobiles allterrain vehicles and sidebysides textron will operate arctic cat as a subsidiary of textron specialized vehicles bell helicopteredit bell  helicopter bell helicopter is an american helicopter and rotorcraft manufacturer headquartered in hurst texas near fort worth ezgoedit ezgo is a designer and manufacturer of light transportation vehicles for golf courses and for other uses products include electric and internal combustion golf carts and multipurpose utility vehicles under the ezgo cushman and bad boy buggy brands greenleeedit greenlee textron is an industrial and electrical tool company headquartered in rockford illinois it was founded in  by brothers robert and ralph greenlee to manufacture their invention a drill surrounded by four chisel blades used in making the pockets for a mortise and tenon joint for the furniture industry in rockford this device is still used in cabinetmaking the bro